1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
3 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 14-140 of Title 70, unless there
4 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
5 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
6 National Guard CareerTech Assistance Act".
7 B. As used in this act:
8 1. "Eligible Guard member" means a current member of the
9 Oklahoma National Guard in good standing who has a high school
10 diploma or who has completed General Educational Development (GED)
11 requirements and who has enrolled in a technology center school;
12 2. "Program" means the Oklahoma National Guard CareerTech
13 Assistance Program established pursuant to the provisions of this
14 act; and
15 3. "Technology center school" means a technology center school
16 district under the governance of the State Board of Career and
17 Technology Education.
18 C. 1. There is hereby created the Oklahoma National Guard
19 CareerTech Assistance Program to provide assistance to eligible
20 Guard members who enroll in a technology center school. Subject to
21 the availability of funds, the amount of assistance shall be
22 equivalent to the amount of tuition for a career and technology
23 program in which the eligible Guard member is enrolled leading to
24
